Wait.

109
00:07:34.579 --> 00:07:37.674
D-d-dead?

110
00:07:37.874 --> 00:07:40.423
I'm sorry to spring it
on you like that. mate

111
00:07:40.627 --> 00:07:42.504
but. uh. now I have it
on good authority

112
00:07:42.712 --> 00:07:44.589
that something ill-natured
is circling you

113
00:07:44.798 --> 00:07:46.596
like a pack of wolves. and I'm
not just gonna sit there

114
00:07:46.800 --> 00:07:48.643
and wait for it to attack.

115
00:07:48.802 --> 00:07:52.477
Why me? I..

116
00:07:52.681 --> 00:07:54.479
Have you noticed I-I teach class

117
00:07:54.683 --> 00:07:56.856
I hold office hours.
and I go home.

118
00:07:57.060 --> 00:08:00.985
And I partake of a whole lot
of sedatives in between.

119
00:08:01.189 --> 00:08:02.987
And that's all I do.

120
00:08:03.191 --> 00:08:04.864
What about the data-mining?

121
00:08:05.068 --> 00:08:06.820
You found any unusual spikes

122
00:08:07.028 --> 00:08:08.371
in activity around
the campus here?

123
00:08:08.571 --> 00:08:10.198
The data-mining.

124
00:08:10.407 --> 00:08:11.954
You know what?

125
00:08:12.158 --> 00:08:13.876
You gaze at
the chaos long enough..

126
00:08:14.077 --> 00:08:17.081
Can swallow you whole.

127
00:08:18.790 --> 00:08:20.713
I shut my program down.

128
00:08:20.917 --> 00:08:23.591
- You shut it down?
- That's right.

129
00:08:23.795 --> 00:08:26.719
You know what I'm focusing
on now? Solutions.

130
00:08:26.923 --> 00:08:28.766
What exactly are those
solutions. Ritchie?

131
00:08:28.967 --> 00:08:31.937
Oh. would you like to hear some.. Here's
the first one.

132
00:08:32.137 --> 00:08:33.639
Solutions.

133
00:08:34.848 --> 00:08:36.065
Yes. Adam.

134
00:08:36.266 --> 00:08:37.688
Professor Simpson.

135
00:08:37.892 --> 00:08:40.862
I need to talk to you about
my office hours today.

136
00:08:41.062 --> 00:08:42.188
My friend Carter

137
00:08:42.397 --> 00:08:44.365
he. uh..

138
00:08:44.566 --> 00:08:46.409
he collapsed outside
of his dorm.

139
00:08:47.152 --> 00:08:48.574
He's dead.

140
00:08:50.155 --> 00:08:51.202
I..

141
00:08:52.490 --> 00:08:53.992
I'm so sorry. Adam.

142
00:08:54.200 --> 00:08:55.952
What happened?

143
00:08:56.161 --> 00:08:57.663
He just..

144
00:08:57.871 --> 00:09:00.499
Stopped breathing.

145
00:09:00.707 --> 00:09:03.677
Well. listen. you-you just.
you take whatever time you need.

146
00:09:03.877 --> 00:09:06.096
Don't worry about your
office hours. okay. Adam?

147
00:09:10.550 --> 00:09:11.426
What's wrong?

148
00:09:11.634 --> 00:09:13.477
I-I. I-I saw someone.

149
00:09:13.678 --> 00:09:15.021
It's okay. there's no one here.

150
00:09:15.221 --> 00:09:17.440
No one but me.

151
00:09:18.475 --> 00:09:19.727
Come here.

152
00:09:19.934 --> 00:09:21.982
It's okay. Shh.

153
00:09:22.187 --> 00:09:23.734
What right do you
have to stop me right here?

154
00:09:23.897 --> 00:09:25.820
- I need to see that boy...
- Just-just get out of here.

155
00:09:26.024 --> 00:09:26.900
- Alright.
- Get out of here!

156
00:09:27.108 --> 00:09:28.075
Cool. Alright.

157
00:09:28.276 --> 00:09:29.869
Your towering respect for law

158
00:09:30.070 --> 00:09:32.368
Is just astounding
as always. John.

159
00:09:32.572 --> 00:09:35.576
Oh. I see you managed to steal
from the cop as well.

160
00:09:35.784 --> 00:09:38.003
It's a campus cop. mate.
big difference.

161
00:09:38.203 --> 00:09:39.750
Let's see. uh. victim collapsed.

162
00:09:39.954 --> 00:09:42.377
Witness found him with blue lips
and extremities.

163
00:09:42.582 --> 00:09:45.802
Says here that's consistent with
a sudden loss of circulation.

164
00:09:46.002 --> 00:09:47.424
- Hmm.
- So you know this bloke?

165
00:09:47.629 --> 00:09:49.723
He was friends with Adam.
my teaching assistant.

166
00:09:49.923 --> 00:09:51.800
Alright. we'll need to
talk to Adam.

167
00:09:52.008 --> 00:09:53.476
Okay. so does that would be

168
00:09:53.676 --> 00:09:55.599
talking meaning talking. right?

169
00:09:55.804 --> 00:09:57.477
- Not harassing..
- Oh. yeah. Well. you know me.

170
00:09:57.680 --> 00:09:59.682
I'm well-versed in the art of
pretending to be a gentleman.

171
00:09:59.891 --> 00:10:03.486
I do know you.
that is debatable. here we go.

172
00:10:07.607 --> 00:10:08.984
I know what I saw.

173
00:10:09.192 --> 00:10:10.990
He was there in the mirror.

174
00:10:11.194 --> 00:10:12.491
Did Adam see him?

175
00:10:12.695 --> 00:10:14.447
No. but he looked like
the man you described

176
00:10:14.656 --> 00:10:16.499
in that house last night.

177
00:10:18.618 --> 00:10:21.337
There was no man. Lily.

178
00:10:21.538 --> 00:10:24.542
And there was no house.
either. it wasn't real.

179
00:10:24.749 --> 00:10:27.628
Wait. wait. last night you said
you saw something. we all did.

180
00:10:30.171 --> 00:10:32.344
We wanted to see something.

181
00:10:32.549 --> 00:10:33.766
It's called group hysteria.

182
00:10:33.967 --> 00:10:37.096
My cognitive psych professor
taught us about it.

183
00:10:37.303 --> 00:10:38.475
When you're just
trying to make sense

184
00:10:38.680 --> 00:10:42.105
out of things that just don't.

185
00:10:42.308 --> 00:10:44.686
I didn't come here
to talk about make-believe.

186
00:10:44.894 --> 00:10:47.397
I came here for Carter.

187
00:10:47.605 --> 00:10:49.778
I need to go clear my head.

188
00:10:49.983 --> 00:10:52.156
Lily. hi.

189
00:10:52.318 --> 00:10:53.365
You got a sec?

190
00:10:53.570 --> 00:10:55.288
Oh. hi. Professor Simpson.

191
00:10:55.488 --> 00:10:56.831
Hey. have you seen Adam?

192
00:10:57.031 --> 00:10:58.374
I've been trying to
call him all day.

193
00:10:58.575 --> 00:11:00.168
Um. I left him in my dorm room.

194
00:11:00.368 --> 00:11:01.540
His phone's probably off.

195
00:11:01.744 --> 00:11:03.621
So. this. uh. chap Carter

196
00:11:03.830 --> 00:11:05.707
he a mate of yours as well?

197
00:11:05.915 --> 00:11:07.132
Oh. it's okay. Lily.

198
00:11:07.333 --> 00:11:08.960
This is my..

199
00:11:09.169 --> 00:11:12.048
Colleague. of
sorts. John Constantine.

200
00:11:12.255 --> 00:11:13.427
I'm just trying
to piece together

201
00:11:13.631 --> 00:11:15.929
what happened to your mate
last night.

202
00:11:16.134 --> 00:11:17.977
It's alright.
You can answer his questions.

203
00:11:18.178 --> 00:11:22.354
I'm confident my associate
is not gonna get you in trouble.

204
00:11:22.557 --> 00:11:23.900
We were at the cemetery.

205
00:11:24.100 --> 00:11:26.523
Look. we were just trying
to have some fun.

206
00:11:26.728 --> 00:11:28.696
Any others with you?

207
00:11:28.897 --> 00:11:30.774
My friend Miranda.

208
00:11:30.982 --> 00:11:32.700
And Adam.
I should get back to him.

209
00:11:32.901 --> 00:11:34.869
He felt terrible
about missing office hours.

210
00:11:35.069 --> 00:11:37.071
He's been taking this project
of yours very seriously...

211
00:11:37.280 --> 00:11:39.123
That's fine. you just
tell him we'll pick back up

212
00:11:39.324 --> 00:11:40.541
when he's ready. alright?

213
00:11:40.700 --> 00:11:42.702
You take care
and have a good night.

214
00:11:42.911 --> 00:11:44.163
Thank you.

215
00:11:47.707 --> 00:11:49.675
So. The cemetery. eh?

216
00:11:49.876 --> 00:11:51.628
- Got what you need. John?
- No. I don't.

217
00:11:51.836 --> 00:11:52.962
She's hiding something

218
00:11:53.171 --> 00:11:54.548
and so are you.

219
00:11:54.756 --> 00:11:56.850
But at least I know
where to start.

220
00:12:22.992 --> 00:12:24.744
Huh. Ha ha.

221
00:12:24.953 --> 00:12:27.047
- Nice landing.
- How's your old friend?

222
00:12:27.247 --> 00:12:29.215
Not very friendly.
to be honest with you.

223
00:12:29.415 --> 00:12:30.962
Maybe that's because
you'd rather wallow in

224
00:12:31.167 --> 00:12:33.590
the dead friends than deal
with them when they're alive.

225
00:12:33.795 --> 00:12:35.843
Uh. you're a bit late
to the party. mate.

226
00:12:36.047 --> 00:12:38.049
Ritchie used to be my ace.

227
00:12:38.258 --> 00:12:39.931
True partner in crime.

228
00:12:40.134 --> 00:12:42.512
All the others were
too easily dazzled. you know?

229
00:12:42.720 --> 00:12:45.064
Used to worship the bloody
ground I walked on.

230
00:12:46.015 --> 00:12:47.141
Modesty.

231
00:12:47.350 --> 00:12:48.852
I thought to myself
here's someone

232
00:12:49.060 --> 00:12:50.357
with a sense of purpose

233
00:12:50.561 --> 00:12:52.780
and twisted enough to face
the darkest forces

234
00:12:52.981 --> 00:12:54.858
that evil has to offer.

235
00:12:59.237 --> 00:13:01.956
Sounds like an interesting basis
for a friendship.

236
00:13:03.408 --> 00:13:06.958
Ah. it's a requirement
with me. mate.

237
00:13:07.161 --> 00:13:09.789
Newcastle left a mark
on our crew.

238
00:13:09.998 --> 00:13:12.672
We all shut down in some way.
but Ritchie's fall..

239
00:13:14.252 --> 00:13:16.129
That was the greatest.

240
00:13:18.798 --> 00:13:20.926
He sounds like he could be
useful to us.

241
00:13:21.134 --> 00:13:23.478
Maybe you can
guide him back into action.

242
00:13:27.598 --> 00:13:31.023
Oh. I'm not exactly a
guiding light. now. am I?

243
00:13:31.227 --> 00:13:32.524
Oh. bollocks.

244
00:13:34.147 --> 00:13:36.946
Really get on
my nerves sometimes.

245
00:13:38.359 --> 00:13:39.906
Alright.

246
00:13:45.616 --> 00:13:47.493
Folde sela levego

247
00:13:48.703 --> 00:13:51.252
hogy igaz legyen reveal

248
00:13:51.456 --> 00:13:53.709
E-te-titok.

249
00:14:53.643 --> 00:14:55.395
- Who's there?
- 'Open the door.

250
00:14:57.230 --> 00:14:59.403
You have to open the door.
quick. before he comes back.

251
00:14:59.607 --> 00:15:01.701
What? Why? Why can't you do it?

252
00:15:04.862 --> 00:15:06.956
Aah!

253
00:15:12.495 --> 00:15:15.044
Beeswax candle.
hieroglyphics and residual ash.

254
00:15:15.248 --> 00:15:16.340
Now. you put those three
together. Ritchie

255
00:15:16.541 --> 00:15:18.293
and what do you get?

256
00:15:18.501 --> 00:15:21.220
- An Egyptian ritual.
- Hm-hm-hmm.

257
00:15:21.421 --> 00:15:23.890
Well. I'm glad to see it's just
your courage that's wavering.

258
00:15:24.090 --> 00:15:25.717
Now. I found those things
in the cemetery

259
00:15:25.925 --> 00:15:27.552
where your. uh. assistant

260
00:15:27.760 --> 00:15:29.182
was having
a skinful last night.

261
00:15:29.387 --> 00:15:30.809
And by the looks of the glyphs.
I'd say it was a ritual

262
00:15:31.013 --> 00:15:32.640
for out-of-body travel.

263
00:15:32.849 --> 00:15:36.023
Now. where do you think that
a bunch of college students

264
