The only rule there

523
00:28:52.481 --> 00:28:55.451
is Shaw... is God.

524
00:28:55.651 --> 00:28:57.699
And it wouldn't be the first one
I've dealt with.

525
00:28:57.903 --> 00:29:00.281
So. shall we?

526
00:29:02.366 --> 00:29:04.243
Ugh! Huh!

527
00:29:16.380 --> 00:29:17.848
Just like back in the day. eh?

528
00:29:18.048 --> 00:29:20.767
Yeah. a little too much like it.

529
00:29:29.685 --> 00:29:32.939
Doo-wat ak-em
ka ren el-bee shoit.

530
00:29:33.146 --> 00:29:35.444
Doo-wat ak-em ma-at.

531
00:29:35.649 --> 00:29:38.619
Doo-wat ak-em
ka ren el-bee shoit.

532
00:29:38.819 --> 00:29:41.368
Doo-wat ak-em ma-at.

533
00:30:48.847 --> 00:30:50.941
- 'Ritchie.
- Aah!

534
00:31:01.777 --> 00:31:03.245
That's the real bogeyman.

535
00:31:03.445 --> 00:31:04.788
Come on.

536
00:31:10.535 --> 00:31:12.458
We need to find Lily now.

537
00:31:16.917 --> 00:31:20.171
- Oh. God..
- Of course. a dead end.

538
00:31:20.379 --> 00:31:22.677
A fitting choice
for our mad architect.

539
00:31:24.132 --> 00:31:25.679
Uh. John. wait.

540
00:31:26.510 --> 00:31:27.762
I can do this.

541
00:31:27.969 --> 00:31:30.438
I studied the principles
of other planes.

542
00:31:31.431 --> 00:31:32.899
I can do this. John.

543
00:31:33.100 --> 00:31:35.398
I can overwrite his world.

544
00:31:36.395 --> 00:31:38.113
I know it.

545
00:31:49.616 --> 00:31:51.960
You're bloody doing it. mate.

546
00:32:00.585 --> 00:32:02.053
Nifty.

547
00:32:02.254 --> 00:32:03.972
Very nifty.

548
00:32:25.360 --> 00:32:27.112
John.

549
00:32:46.047 --> 00:32:47.640
Please.

550
00:32:47.841 --> 00:32:48.967
Hide me.

551
00:32:49.801 --> 00:32:51.678
He's watching.

552
00:32:52.762 --> 00:32:54.014
Who are you?

553
00:32:54.222 --> 00:32:55.940
Where's Shaw?

554
00:33:08.528 --> 00:33:09.871
I'm Jacob Shaw.

555
00:33:10.071 --> 00:33:12.119
And who are you?

556
00:33:22.501 --> 00:33:24.799
So the legend's true.

557
00:33:25.003 --> 00:33:26.971
You did come here to escape.

558
00:33:27.172 --> 00:33:29.220
I came here to live.

559
00:33:29.424 --> 00:33:31.768
You're an arrogant.
bloody sod. aren't you?

560
00:33:31.968 --> 00:33:33.641
You're here to
mutilate and murder.

561
00:33:33.845 --> 00:33:36.268
Beings of my own creation.

562
00:33:36.473 --> 00:33:38.100
Those students you butchered

563
00:33:38.308 --> 00:33:40.811
they didn't just leap out
of your imagination.

564
00:33:41.019 --> 00:33:41.861
They were flesh and blood.

565
00:33:42.020 --> 00:33:45.240
Yes. and they invaded my space.

566
00:33:45.440 --> 00:33:48.068
My world. my rules.

567
00:33:48.276 --> 00:33:49.448
It's a lesson
you're about to learn.

568
00:33:49.653 --> 00:33:53.328
Oh. boy. you are a waste. man.

569
00:33:53.532 --> 00:33:56.251
And you're just a psychopath.
hacking up..

570
00:33:59.663 --> 00:34:02.462
Aah! Agh! Agh!

571
00:34:02.666 --> 00:34:04.088
A-agh!

572
00:34:04.292 --> 00:34:05.418
Ugh!

573
00:34:07.295 --> 00:34:09.263
These wounds. Ritchie.
they're his reality. not yours.

574
00:34:09.464 --> 00:34:10.761
You're the greater mind here.

575
00:34:10.966 --> 00:34:12.434
You can beat this guy.

576
00:34:12.634 --> 00:34:13.476
Ritchie.

577
00:34:13.677 --> 00:34:15.554
In this place. you..

578
00:34:16.680 --> 00:34:18.102
You decide.

579
00:34:18.306 --> 00:34:20.274
Ritchie. look at me.
Look at me.

580
00:34:20.475 --> 00:34:22.694
Ritchie. look at me. Look at me.

581
00:34:24.396 --> 00:34:27.275
I believe in you. old son.

582
00:34:27.482 --> 00:34:29.029
Now. bloody do it!

583
00:34:29.234 --> 00:34:31.157
- Unh!
- Do it!

584
00:34:46.251 --> 00:34:49.300
Some god you turned out
to be. Shaw.

585
00:34:50.880 --> 00:34:53.178
You forgot the sun.

586
00:34:53.383 --> 00:34:54.680
No..

587
00:34:59.639 --> 00:35:02.108
- No!
- Oh. yes.

588
00:35:03.602 --> 00:35:05.604
All this time you spent here

589
00:35:05.812 --> 00:35:08.065
you could've been
building worlds.

590
00:35:08.273 --> 00:35:11.948
You could've been redefining
life and how we live it.

591
00:35:12.110 --> 00:35:15.535
And the day you gave into
your weakness. Shaw..

592
00:35:15.739 --> 00:35:18.709
that was the day
you became obsolete.

593
00:35:18.908 --> 00:35:20.910
This is my world!

594
00:35:22.120 --> 00:35:23.963
Not anymore.

595
00:35:32.839 --> 00:35:34.136
We have to get out of here.

596
00:35:34.341 --> 00:35:35.888
This way. mate. come on.

597
00:35:39.346 --> 00:35:40.268
Come on. Ritchie.

598
00:35:40.472 --> 00:35:41.439
(0K3)!-

599
00:36:02.661 --> 00:36:04.334
Nice job. Ritchie.

600
00:36:04.537 --> 00:36:06.585
You even got
the temperature right.

601
00:36:07.749 --> 00:36:09.171
Lily.

602
00:36:14.506 --> 00:36:15.632
What's happening?

603
00:36:15.840 --> 00:36:17.012
Shaw's world is collapsing.

604
00:36:17.175 --> 00:36:19.177
We need to get out of here
right now. Let's go!

605
00:36:21.388 --> 00:36:23.311
What are you doing?
We have to go!

606
00:36:24.265 --> 00:36:26.359
This is as far as we go.

607
00:36:26.559 --> 00:36:29.358
No. No! No! No!

608
00:36:29.562 --> 00:36:31.781
No! No! No!

609
00:36:31.981 --> 00:36:34.985
No! they're all still in there!
We have to do something!

610
00:36:35.193 --> 00:36:36.695
There's nothing we can do
for them.

611
00:36:36.903 --> 00:36:38.780
Come on! it's too late!

612
00:36:49.374 --> 00:36:52.002
Nothing we could've done. Lily.

613
00:36:52.210 --> 00:36:54.508
They only existed
inside that house.

614
00:36:54.713 --> 00:36:56.215
Shaw's gone forever.

615
00:36:56.423 --> 00:36:58.391
Their souls are free now.

616
00:36:58.591 --> 00:37:00.810
On to the next journey.

617
00:37:01.010 --> 00:37:02.512
Look at me.

618
00:37:36.129 --> 00:37:39.224
- It's your turn.
- Oh... hold on a minute. squire.

619
00:37:39.424 --> 00:37:41.768
And if I go back..

620
00:37:41.968 --> 00:37:43.766
What happens to you?

621
00:37:46.931 --> 00:37:48.933
I stay here.

622
00:37:55.815 --> 00:37:58.819
Here happens to be
an elaborate figment

623
00:37:59.027 --> 00:38:01.246
of your confused imagination.

624
00:38:02.655 --> 00:38:04.578
What was it
you said to me in there?

625
00:38:05.617 --> 00:38:07.836
I decide what's real.

626
00:38:09.621 --> 00:38:11.168
This is it.

627
00:38:11.372 --> 00:38:14.125
John. this is the reality
that I want.

628
00:38:15.251 --> 00:38:16.252
Simplicity.

629
00:38:16.461 --> 00:38:19.340
And... endless possibility.

630
00:38:19.547 --> 00:38:21.845
This. John. this is.
this is paradise.

631
00:38:22.050 --> 00:38:24.144
Oh. what makes you think
that after a decade

632
00:38:24.344 --> 00:38:26.517
you won't go off
your trolley like Shaw?

633
00:38:27.639 --> 00:38:29.892
Shaw was mad to begin with.

634
00:38:30.099 --> 00:38:31.476
I'll do it right.

635
00:38:31.684 --> 00:38:33.561
I'll build a world here.

636
00:38:33.770 --> 00:38:38.150
I'll invent
and create and thrive.

637
00:38:40.819 --> 00:38:44.699
You know what? I've already lost
one good friend to this fight.

638
00:38:44.906 --> 00:38:47.659
And I'm not losing another. so
I'm calling you on your rubbish

639
00:38:47.867 --> 00:38:49.835
Ritchie Simpson.
if you stay here..

640
00:38:51.037 --> 00:38:53.415
You will go balmy.

641
00:38:53.623 --> 00:38:56.627
Balmier than you already are.
if that's at all possible.

642
00:38:59.295 --> 00:39:01.514
Better here than back home.

643
00:39:03.800 --> 00:39:07.020
At least. in this world..

644
00:39:07.220 --> 00:39:08.722
I can forget about the darkness

645
00:39:08.930 --> 00:39:10.853
closing in on us. John.

646
00:39:13.142 --> 00:39:15.315
Look. I just don't..

647
00:39:15.520 --> 00:39:18.194
I don't want to be afraid
anymore. John.

648
00:39:19.691 --> 00:39:21.159
Fine.

649
00:39:21.943 --> 00:39:23.320
That's fine.

650
00:39:23.528 --> 00:39:25.906
Indulge yourself. Ritchie.

651
00:39:26.114 --> 00:39:27.832
Just like Shaw.

652
00:39:28.032 --> 00:39:30.660
You're two visionary peas
in a bloody pod.

653
00:39:30.869 --> 00:39:32.667
But do me a favor.

654
00:39:34.747 --> 00:39:37.296
Don't lie to yourself.

655
00:39:37.500 --> 00:39:40.003
This isn't about
you creating something new.

656
00:39:41.713 --> 00:39:44.432
This is about you running away.

657
00:40:00.815 --> 00:40:02.283
Ritchie?

658
00:40:02.483 --> 00:40:05.157
Ritchie. Ritchie. Ritchie.
Ritchie.

659
00:40:05.361 --> 00:40:07.113
Come on. come back to me.

660
00:40:07.322 --> 00:40:09.199
Come on. Ritchie.
come on. man. come on.

661
00:40:09.407 --> 00:40:12.035
Come on. come back to me.
Come back. Ritchie!

662
00:40:37.393 --> 00:40:38.940
Ugh!

663
00:40:45.610 --> 00:40:47.612
Oh. you bugger.

664
00:41:28.236 --> 00:41:31.866
In our last class. we touched on
the subject of nirvana.

665
00:41:32.824 --> 00:41:35.168
Achieving enlightenment.

666
00:41:35.368 --> 00:41:37.621
In order to do that..

667
00:41:37.829 --> 00:41:40.207
Certain truths must be accepted.

668
00:41:41.833 --> 00:41:43.380
First and foremost..

669
00:41:44.502 --> 00:41:46.880
Suffering is unavoidable.

670
00:41:47.922 --> 00:41:49.014
Secondly

671
00:41:49.173 --> 00:41:51.301
you must understand

672
00:41:51.509 --> 00:41:53.807
that suffering is caused
by craving.

673
00:41:56.014 --> 00:41:59.109
Humankind desires relief in ways

674
00:41:59.308 --> 00:42:02.437
that ultimately do not
satisfy the soul.

675
00:42:04.313 --> 00:42:06.486
The third and final truth

676
00:42:06.691 --> 00:42:10.241
is that inner peace is possible.

677
00:42:10.445 --> 00:42:14.120
But humankind's suffering
won't end

678
00:42:14.323 --> 00:42:17.372
until we learn
how to stop our desire.

679
00:42:17.396 --> 00:42:19.396
http://hiqve.com/
